	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I also recommend Nerdy Nights.  I'd also check out Blargg's NES tutorial (It was on this forum somewhere...) Basically read a bunch of docs.  It'll start to click.
<br />
<br />Basically, for me, I haven't found one tutorial that is/was "the one", but Nerdy Nights is the closest, mainly thanks to the images.  The GBAGuy ones... not so much.
<br />
<br />I learned a lot by setting little goals for myself, like "I'm going to display a sprite"  "I'm going to animate that sprite" "I'm going to move that sprite" "I'm going to make that sprite flip when I turn around because chances are I'm not going to make a game starring Michael Jackson."

		

		</td>
	</tr>
